body:
Fixes #17921.

## Release notes summary - What our users need to know

`http get` auto-parses responses by looking up a `from <subtype>` command. For `application/x-nuon` (the [documented MIME type](https://www.nushell.sh/book/loading_data.html#nuon) for nuon), `subtype()` returns `"x-nuon"` — but `from x-nuon` does not exist.

Strip the `x-` prefix before the lookup so `application/x-nuon` → `from nuon`, `application/x-yaml` → `from yaml`, etc.

```rust
// before
_ => Some(content_type.subtype().to_string()),

// after
_ => {
    let subtype = content_type.subtype().as_str();
    Some(subtype.strip_prefix("x-").unwrap_or(subtype).to_string())
}
```
